<div class="row">
	<div class="col-xs-12 news-content no-padding">






<figure>
	<img alt="Bank of England Governor Andrew Bailey" class="img-responsive imported-news-entry-img" src="https://images2.markets.businessinsider.com/60c7855a23393a00188e2fa5?format=jpeg">
<figcaption>Bank of England Governor Andrew Bailey.
<p class="copyright">Photo by TOLGA AKMEN/POOL/AFP via Getty Images<!-- sh_cad_1 --></p>
</figcaption>
</figure><ul class="summary-list">
<li>Bank of England Governor Andrew Bailey said cryptocurrencies are not a good method of payment, Bloomberg reported.</li>
<li>&#34;If you want to buy them then please understand that you can lose, you could lose all your money,&#34; he said.</li>
<li>This isn&#39;t the first time the governor has expressed skepticism towards cryptocurrencies. </li>
</ul>
<ul class="summary-list">
<li><a href="https://newsletter.businessinsider.com/join/4np/10-things-opening-bell?utm_source=markets&utm_medium=ingest" target="_blank"><strong>Sign up here for our daily newsletter, 10 Things Before the Opening Bell</strong></a><strong>.</strong></li>
</ul><!-- sh_cad_2 --><p>Bank of England Governor Andrew Bailey said he believes that cryptocurrencies are not a reliable method of payment, highlighting their high volatility in comments made on Monday.<!-- sh_cad_3 --></p><p>&#34;They fluctuate in value substantially,&#34; he said during a virtual conference, <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-06-14/crypto-currencies-not-good-medium-for-payments-boe-chief-says?srnd=markets-vp" target="_blank">reported by Bloomberg</a>. &#34;Which is why they&#39;re, on the whole, not a good medium for making payments.&#34;<!-- sh_cad_4 --></p><p>Bailey&#39;s comment comes days after lawmakers in El Salvador voted to make bitcoin legal tender alongside the US dollar, the first country in the world to do so. <!-- sh_cad_5 --></p><p>&#34;Given the volatility of the asset value, and given the fact that there isn&#39;t a real asset underpinning them, I&#39;m afraid if you want to buy them then please understand that you can lose, you could lose all your money,&#34; Bailey said.<!-- sh_cad_6 -->
		<div class="htl-ad-placeholder htl-ad-placeholder--desktopInPost htl-ad" data-unit="Markets-Insider/Currencies/News" data-sizes="0x0:|960x0:300x250,600x480|1200x0:728x90,800x480" data-prebid="0x0:|960x0:Currencies/News/medrec|1200x0:Currencies/News/leaderboard" data-targeting='{"region":"Desktop In Post Ad","amp_check":"false"}' data-refresh="viewable" data-refresh-secs=""></div>

		<div class="htl-ad-placeholder htl-ad-placeholder--mobileInPost htl-ad" data-unit="Markets-Insider/Currencies/News" data-sizes="0x0:300x50,300x100,300x150,320x50,320x100,320x150,300x250|768x0:" data-prebid="0x0:Currencies/News/medrec_flex|768x0:" data-targeting='{"region":"Mobile In Post Ad","amp_check":"false"}' data-refresh="viewable" data-refresh-secs=""></div>
</p><p>Bitcoin on Monday moved past<a href="https://markets.businessinsider.com/currencies/news/bitcoin-price-elon-musk-tesla-resume-crypto-payments-clean-energy-2021-6-1030518811?utm_source=markets&utm_medium=ingest" target="_blank"> $40,000 </a>after Elon Musk suggested <a href="https://markets.businessinsider.com/currencies/news/bitcoin-price-elon-musk-tesla-resume-crypto-payments-clean-energy-2021-6-1030518811?utm_source=markets&utm_medium=ingest" target="_blank">Tesla might accept it as payment again</a> once mining can be done using cleaner energy. <!-- sh_cad_7 --></p><p>Musk&#39;s reversal on accepting <a href="https://markets.businessinsider.com/currencies/btc-usd?utm_source=markets&utm_medium=ingest?utm_source=markets&utm_medium=ingest?utm_source=markets&utm_medium=ingest" target="_blank" rel="noopener">bitcoin</a> as payment in mid-May sent shockwaves across the digital asset ecosystem and sent the price of bitcoin into a nosedive. <!-- sh_cad_8 --></p><p>&#34;We&#39;re going to engage with users, the technology sector, to understand the potential for these things,&#34; Bailey said. &#34;And there&#39;s a lot of work going on in the Bank of England to understand the implications of them for central banking.&#34;<!-- sh_cad_9 --></p><p>This isn&#39;t the first time the BoE governor has expressed skepticism towards cryptocurrencies. <!-- sh_cad_10 --></p><p>In May, he told journalists that <a href="https://markets.businessinsider.com/currencies/news/cryptocurrencies-bitcoin-dogecoin-risks-lose-money-bank-of-england-andrew-bailey-1030396958?utm_source=markets&utm_medium=ingest" target="_blank">cryptocurrencies have &#34;no intrinsic value&#34;</a> and that people should only buy them if they are prepared to lose all their money.<!-- sh_cad_11 -->
		<div class="htl-ad-placeholder htl-ad-placeholder--desktopInPost htl-ad" data-unit="Markets-Insider/Currencies/News" data-sizes="0x0:|960x0:300x250,600x480|1200x0:728x90,800x480" data-prebid="0x0:|960x0:Currencies/News/medrec|1200x0:Currencies/News/leaderboard" data-targeting='{"region":"Desktop In Post Ad","amp_check":"false"}' data-refresh="viewable" data-refresh-secs=""></div>

